summaries.short: Dory wakes up to a terrifying new reality, while Portia, Elliott, and Drew grow impatient with their seemingly AWOL “friend.”
summaries.full: After getting kidnapped at the end of last season, Dory wakes up to find herself face-to-face with her obsessed fan and plunged into a terrifying new reality. Meanwhile, an increasingly impatient Portia and Elliott throw a party for a seemingly AWOL Dory, and Drew's family takes him out for a nice dinner to celebrate the court’s not-guilty verdict.

summaries.short: Alarming evidence surfaces that potentially obliterates Dory and Drew's chances of being acquitted. Elliott confronts his roots, and Portia attempts to make amends for testifying against her friends.

summaries.full: Dory tries to escape from her felt prison and the obsessed fan we now know as Chip. Meanwhile, Drew starts a new life at a theme park as “Prince Grisly,” Portia auditions to be “Portia” in the film adaptation of the trial, and Elliott reconsiders his political beliefs for a chance to host his own news talk show.
